---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import DocsSubnav from '../../components/DocsSubnav.astro';
import MythicDivider from '../../components/MythicDivider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Docs · Quickstart"
  description="Install Zana, wire it into Claude Code, and run your first agent — in under five minutes."
>
  <DocsSubnav />

  <section class="container-zana py-16">
    <p class="ornament text-xs text-gold">— quickstart —</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-5xl text-forest md:text-6xl">First five minutes with Zana.</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-moss leading-relaxed">
      Two paths, same primitives. <strong>Native</strong> — install the plugin
      and start orchestrating from any Claude Code chat. <strong>Daemon</strong>
      — install the CLI when you need headless / CI / cron. Most users start
      native; the daemon is opt-in.
    </p>

    <article class="prose-zana mt-12 max-w-prose space-y-12">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">Prerequisites</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-moss">
          <li>· <strong>Node.js 20+</strong> (<code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">node -v</code>)</li>
          <li>· <strong>npm</strong> (bundled with Node)</li>
          <li>· <strong>git</strong></li>
          <li>· <strong>Claude Code CLI</strong> — recommended (<code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">claude --version</code>)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">1. Install the plugins (native path)</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">If you have Claude Code already, this is all you need to start orchestrating. No daemon, no MCP, no build.</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code" lang="bash">{`/plugin marketplace add grebmann1/zana
/plugin install zana@zana-marketplace        # orchestrator (27 commands, 2 skills)
/plugin install zana-loop@zana-marketplace   # lightweight /loop scheduling (3 commands, 1 skill)

# then restart Claude Code so the new commands register`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">After restart, type <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">/zana</code> and you'll see the team, autopilot, council, ticket, schedule, and loop families. Slash commands drive Claude Code's native <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">Agent</code> + <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">SendMessage</code> primitives — no separate process.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">2. Install the daemon + CLI <span class="text-base text-moss font-normal">(optional — headless / CI / cron)</span></h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">Skip this section unless you need scheduled tasks, autopilot loops, or non-interactive runs that must outlive any chat.</p>

        <p class="mt-6 text-moss text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gold">— from npm (fastest) —</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="terminal" lang="bash">{`npm install -g @zana-ai/mcp
# pulls in @zana-ai/{core,work,extras,intelligence,swarm,server} as deps
# postinstall registers the MCP server in ~/.claude/settings.json`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss text-sm">No clone, no build. The package's <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">postinstall</code> wires the MCP server automatically. After install, run <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">zana init wizard</code> in the workspace you want to bootstrap.</p>

        <p class="mt-6 text-moss text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gold">— from source (full repo) —</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="terminal" lang="bash">{`git clone https://github.com/grebmann1/zana.git
cd zana
bash scripts/install.sh

# or remote-pipe (no clone)
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/grebmann1/zana/main/scripts/install.sh | bash`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">The installer runs <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">npm install</code>, <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">npm run build:runtime</code>, <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">npm install -g .</code> (puts <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">zana</code> on your PATH), <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">claude mcp add zana</code>, and finally <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">zana init wizard --repair-mcp</code> for <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">$PWD</code>.</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss text-sm">Useful flags: <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">--workspace &lt;path&gt;</code>, <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">--no-init</code>, <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">--no-setup-mcp</code>, <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">--no-doctor</code>. See <a href="https://github.com/grebmann1/zana/blob/main/INSTALL.md#path-b--manual-per-step-scriptable-for-agents" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-forest hover:text-berry font-semibold">INSTALL.md</a> for the manual per-step path.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">3. Verify</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">Native — type <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">/zana</code> in Claude Code; you should see the slash menu (team, autopilot, council, ticket, schedule, loop). Then run a smoke team:</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code" lang="text">{`/zana:team backend-squad "Reply with PONG"
# spawns a curated team in this session via Agent + SendMessage`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-4 text-moss">Daemon (only if you installed step 2):</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="terminal" lang="bash">{`zana status                           # ●  <id>  port:474XX  pid:<pid>
claude mcp list | grep zana           # zana: ... ✓ Connected
claude plugin details zana@zana-marketplace | head -5`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">If <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">claude mcp list</code> shows <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">✗ Failed to connect</code>, the runtime build is stale — rerun <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">npm run build:runtime</code>.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">4. Spawn your first agent</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">Native — one slash command. The team template spawns a curated set of background agents, each with a name, a profile-derived system prompt, and SendMessage handoffs.</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code" lang="text">{`/zana:team backend-squad "Add a /healthz endpoint"
# → Spawning architect, backend-dev, backend-dev-2, test-writer …`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-4 text-moss">Daemon — one MCP call (only available with step 2 installed). <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">zana_oneshot_query</code> spawns a profile, waits for output, returns the answer.</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code · MCP (daemon path)" lang="text">{`zana_oneshot_query({
  profileId: "researcher",
  prompt: "Reply with the single word: PONG",
  timeout: 90000
})
// → "PONG"`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">If you see <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">"PONG"</code>, your daemon install is good.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">Where to next</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">Pick the path that matches your work.</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-moss">
          <li>· <a href="/docs/recipes/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry font-semibold">Recipes</a> — copy-paste end-to-end examples for tickets, schedules, autopilot, deliberation. Each one mirrored by a live Claude integration test.</li>
          <li>· <a href="/docs/concepts/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry font-semibold">Concepts</a> — deliberation, schedules, /loop vs daemon, runtime adapter.</li>
          <li>· <a href="/docs/cli/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry font-semibold">CLI reference</a> — drive Zana from the terminal (CI, scripts, ops).</li>
          <li>· <a href="/how-it-works/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry">How it works</a> — primitives in depth.</li>
          <li>· <a href="https://github.com/grebmann1/zana" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-forest hover:text-berry">GitHub repo</a> — issues, profiles, contributions.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <MythicDivider />
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
